                <head>No. 175.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Sargent</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-02-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 15, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President invites Germany to send a commission of experts to the United
                    States to examine raising and packing of hogs and hog products for food. He asks
                    that final decision in prohibitory measures be suspended until commission can
                    adequately report.</p>
                <p>Instruction by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
